body:
_Part of #9274 onboarding with Keycard epic (mark as checked there, when closing this issue)_

- Suggesting new copy to help address the possible question the user might have:

```
Confirm the seed phrase
Write down word #3 below. Just to help you make sure you backed up the seed phrase down correctly
```

- Is it okay that it's possible to go back and see the seed phrase again? If not, it should be "Cancel" instead of the "back" icon;
- The layout should be fixed according to Figma. The word is vertically and horizontally centered;
- The keyboard should never disappear on this screen;
- There should only be "Next >" in the toolbar, no "< Back";
- The error message should be shown according to Figma. It should say "Wrong word" and select the word, to help users enter a different word without having to manually erase the incorrect one;
- After the incorrect word is erased, the "Wrong word" error **should disappear**. This is especially important on small screens since there the error tooltip might overlap the subheading;

